2
00:01:20,460 --> 00:01:28,580
Arsenal Military Academy

3
00:01:28,860 --> 00:01:31,580
Episode 22

4
00:01:38,720 --> 00:01:39,640
Excuse me,

5
00:01:39,800 --> 00:01:41,530
which is Xie Liangchen's room?

6
00:01:41,920 --> 00:01:42,680
Over there.

7
00:01:44,039 --> 00:01:44,680
Thanks.

8
00:01:44,680 --> 00:01:45,610
You're welcome.

9
00:02:12,960 --> 00:02:13,480
Come in.

10
00:02:16,920 --> 00:02:17,600
Ms. Huo.

11
00:02:23,320 --> 00:02:24,640
How did you get hurt?

12
00:02:25,440 --> 00:02:26,480
Bad luck I guess.

13
00:02:27,440 --> 00:02:28,920
Thank you for coming.

14
00:02:29,200 --> 00:02:30,260
I know you're busy.

15
00:02:30,680 --> 00:02:32,079
Not at all, I should come.

16
00:02:33,280 --> 00:02:34,120
Luckily,

17
00:02:34,320 --> 00:02:35,450
You've made it back.

18
00:02:35,480 --> 00:02:36,720
I was worried about you.

19
00:02:36,720 --> 00:02:38,120
Be careful in the future.

20
00:02:38,640 --> 00:02:39,280
I will.

21
00:02:40,280 --> 00:02:41,960
I've granted Xiaojun's leave.

22
00:02:41,960 --> 00:02:44,079
She'll take care of you.

23
00:02:44,280 --> 00:02:45,010
Thanks a lot.

24
00:02:45,680 --> 00:02:47,040
Don't mention it.

25
00:02:49,160 --> 00:02:49,720
Lie down.

26
00:02:49,960 --> 00:02:51,360
You need to rest.

27
00:02:52,800 --> 00:02:53,560
I'm fine.

28
00:02:54,079 --> 00:02:54,720
Be good.

29
00:02:56,360 --> 00:02:56,880
Fine.

30
00:03:01,680 --> 00:03:02,480
Thanks.

31
00:03:09,960 --> 00:03:10,920
Feel better now?

32
00:03:14,920 --> 00:03:15,480
Alright,

33
00:03:16,240 --> 00:03:18,480
now that you're safe, I can stop worrying.

34
00:03:18,480 --> 00:03:19,200
I'm leaving.

35
00:03:19,200 --> 00:03:20,040
Bye, Ms. Huo.

36
00:03:20,720 --> 00:03:21,320
Take care.

37
00:03:31,120 --> 00:03:32,650
The patient is recovering.

38
00:03:32,720 --> 00:03:34,760
But he needs more nutrition.

39
00:03:34,960 --> 00:03:36,420
And he still needs to rest.

40
00:03:36,760 --> 00:03:37,560
Thank you, doctor.

41
00:03:37,560 --> 00:03:38,800
We'll need to keep him here for a few more days.

42
00:03:38,800 --> 00:03:39,280
OK.

43
00:04:24,760 --> 00:04:25,480
Junshan.

44
00:04:27,360 --> 00:04:28,690
How can you still laugh?

45
00:04:30,240 --> 00:04:31,240
I'm back alive.

46
00:04:31,240 --> 00:04:32,280
Can't I laugh?

47
00:04:34,040 --> 00:04:34,770
Does it hurt?

48
00:04:36,680 --> 00:04:37,340
Not so much.

49
00:04:38,960 --> 00:04:39,640
Liar!

50
00:04:40,800 --> 00:04:42,130
What exactly happened?

51
00:04:42,159 --> 00:04:43,520
You were sent to escort medicine.

52
00:04:43,520 --> 00:04:44,880
Why were you hunted?

53
00:04:45,320 --> 00:04:46,680
I don't know, either.

54
00:04:47,520 --> 00:04:49,800
I guess their aim is not us.

55
00:04:50,360 --> 00:04:52,000
There is something on Xie Liangchen

56
00:04:52,000 --> 00:04:53,200
that they want.

57
00:04:53,680 --> 00:04:54,740
So they followed us

58
00:04:55,040 --> 00:04:56,400
to get it back.

59
00:04:56,640 --> 00:04:57,840
Where is it now?

60
00:04:57,840 --> 00:04:58,880
Who has it?

61
00:05:03,920 --> 00:05:05,980
I fear they'll come to hurt you again.

62
00:05:08,040 --> 00:05:09,040
Liangchen has it.

63
00:05:09,760 --> 00:05:12,220
We'll give it to Sergeant Lv once he arrives.

64
00:05:13,240 --> 00:05:14,120
That's good.

65
00:05:14,600 --> 00:05:15,800
An innocent man gets into trouble

66
00:05:15,800 --> 00:05:17,060
because of his wealth.

67
00:05:17,640 --> 00:05:18,280
Right now,

68
00:05:18,560 --> 00:05:19,820
safety is everything.

69
00:05:20,840 --> 00:05:21,720
You're right.

70
00:05:22,920 --> 00:05:23,800
Are you hungry?

71
00:05:24,280 --> 00:05:25,200
It's lunchtime.

72
00:05:25,200 --> 00:05:26,480
I'll buy you some food.

73
00:05:28,160 --> 00:05:29,160
I'm a bit hungry.

74
00:05:29,160 --> 00:05:30,000
Wait for me.

75
00:05:30,000 --> 00:05:30,600
I'll be back soon.

76
00:05:30,600 --> 00:05:31,240
OK.

77
00:05:53,040 --> 00:05:53,900
The door is open

78
00:05:54,080 --> 00:05:55,080
so I didn't knock.

79
00:05:57,400 --> 00:05:58,400
Do you need help?

80
00:06:00,960 --> 00:06:01,480
Yeah.

81
00:06:01,800 --> 00:06:02,480
Thanks.

82
00:06:28,200 --> 00:06:28,760
Here.

83
00:06:29,240 --> 00:06:29,880
Thank you.

84
00:06:31,960 --> 00:06:33,120
How's your wound?

85
00:06:34,600 --> 00:06:35,920
I got shot in the thigh.

86
00:06:36,360 --> 00:06:37,690
It'll heal in a few days.

87
00:06:37,760 --> 00:06:38,920
You got shot?

88
00:06:39,320 --> 00:06:40,450
Will it leave a scar?

89
00:06:41,040 --> 00:06:42,120
I guess so.

90
00:06:43,200 --> 00:06:44,040
What a pity!

91
00:06:46,320 --> 00:06:47,400
I'm a man.

92
00:06:47,520 --> 00:06:48,600
Having a scar is no big deal.

93
00:06:48,600 --> 00:06:49,930
I'm not like your girls.

94
00:06:51,360 --> 00:06:52,920
You're good-looking.

95
00:06:53,159 --> 00:06:54,620
You're as pretty as a girl.

96
00:06:55,120 --> 00:06:56,320
It'll be a shame

97
00:06:56,720 --> 00:06:58,080
if you're disfigured!

98
00:06:59,560 --> 00:07:01,290
Luckily, your leg took the hit.

99
00:07:01,880 --> 00:07:03,480
You came to check on Junshan?

100
00:07:04,560 --> 00:07:05,520
How is he?

101
00:07:06,160 --> 00:07:07,020
The same as you,

102
00:07:07,320 --> 00:07:09,160
pretending that it's not a big deal.

103
00:07:09,160 --> 00:07:10,920
I'm worried sick!

104
00:07:12,520 --> 00:07:13,800
You boys

105
00:07:14,360 --> 00:07:15,160
are all alike.

106
00:07:21,960 --> 00:07:23,160
You want more?

107
00:07:23,720 --> 00:07:24,360
I'm good.

108
00:07:27,080 --> 00:07:27,680
Thank you.

109
00:07:29,120 --> 00:07:29,880
Are you OK?

110
00:07:29,880 --> 00:07:30,720
I'm fine. I'm OK.

111
00:07:30,720 --> 00:07:32,440
Don't move. Don't move. I'll call the nurse.

112
00:07:32,440 --> 00:07:33,040
Nurse.

113
00:07:33,320 --> 00:07:34,000
Nurse.

114
00:07:34,680 --> 00:07:35,720
Hello, may I help you?

115
00:07:35,720 --> 00:07:37,040
Please bring me another quilt.

116
00:07:37,040 --> 00:07:37,680
OK.

117
00:07:39,280 --> 00:07:40,360
Are you scalded?

118
00:07:40,360 --> 00:07:41,040
I'm fine.

119
00:07:41,240 --> 00:07:42,040
Is your leg OK?

120
00:07:42,159 --> 00:07:42,680
Yeah.

121
00:07:42,680 --> 00:07:43,880
Where's the towel? Dry your hands.

122
00:07:43,880 --> 00:07:45,080
Under the bed. I can get it myself.

123
00:07:45,080 --> 00:07:45,960
Thank you.

124
00:07:54,360 --> 00:07:54,840
Thanks.

125
00:07:54,840 --> 00:07:55,640
You're welcome.

126
00:07:55,640 --> 00:07:56,900
Thank you. Let me do it.

127
00:07:57,600 --> 00:07:58,200
OK.

128
00:08:04,000 --> 00:08:05,440
I'm sorry. It's my fault.

129
00:08:05,440 --> 00:08:06,360
I was clumsy.

130
00:08:06,480 --> 00:08:06,960
It's OK.

131
00:08:06,960 --> 00:08:08,320
Look, it's all changed.

132
00:08:10,000 --> 00:08:11,080
I shall leave then.

133
00:08:11,200 --> 00:08:12,930
I need to buy lunch for Junshan.

134
00:08:13,600 --> 00:08:14,320
Go ahead.

135
00:08:14,320 --> 00:08:15,600
Do you want something to eat?

136
00:08:15,600 --> 00:08:16,240
No, thanks.

137
00:08:16,240 --> 00:08:18,120
Xiaojun went back to get my lunch.

138
00:08:18,480 --> 00:08:19,120
Alright then.

139
00:08:19,120 --> 00:08:20,200
Get some rest.

140
00:08:20,560 --> 00:08:21,360
See you later.

141
00:08:21,520 --> 00:08:22,080
Bye.

142
00:08:22,480 --> 00:08:23,320
Bye.

143
00:09:00,240 --> 00:09:02,240
I saw Jin Xianrong outside just now.

144
00:09:02,920 --> 00:09:04,250
What was she doing here?

145
00:09:04,760 --> 00:09:05,840
She came to visit.

146
00:09:06,120 --> 00:09:08,250
I don't believe she could be that nice.

147
00:09:09,560 --> 00:09:10,560
What's for lunch?

148
00:09:13,880 --> 00:09:14,800
Smells good.

149
00:09:17,120 --> 00:09:17,920
Great!

150
00:09:18,240 --> 00:09:19,080
This is it.

151
00:09:20,200 --> 00:09:21,560
Inform Mr. James,

152
00:09:22,160 --> 00:09:23,360
2 p.m. this afternoon

153
00:09:23,920 --> 00:09:24,850
at Jinhua Hotel.

154
00:09:25,280 --> 00:09:25,920
Yes.

155
00:09:35,320 --> 00:09:36,040
Finished.

156
00:09:36,120 --> 00:09:36,850
Are you full?

157
00:09:37,440 --> 00:09:38,640
I'm going to explode.

158
00:09:39,080 --> 00:09:40,340
Here, wipe your mouth.

159
00:09:42,400 --> 00:09:43,460
I'll go wash these.

160
00:09:50,120 --> 00:09:50,880
Be careful.

161
00:10:02,800 --> 00:10:03,600
Shen Junshan,

162
00:10:04,960 --> 00:10:05,920
why are you here?

163
00:10:06,040 --> 00:10:07,240
I came to check on you.

164
00:10:08,280 --> 00:10:09,360
How do you feel?

165
00:10:10,840 --> 00:10:11,800
I'm better now.

166
00:10:15,760 --> 00:10:16,440
Hey,

167
00:10:16,840 --> 00:10:19,000
did you call your family?

168
00:10:19,800 --> 00:10:20,480
No.

169
00:10:20,960 --> 00:10:22,360
My parents are back home.

170
00:10:22,360 --> 00:10:23,960
I don't want to trouble them.

171
00:10:24,040 --> 00:10:25,160
I'm fine anyway.

172
00:10:25,440 --> 00:10:26,640
No need to worry them.

173
00:10:28,080 --> 00:10:30,010
Then who's been taking care of you?

174
00:10:30,600 --> 00:10:31,320
My friend

175
00:10:31,320 --> 00:10:32,080
Tan Xiaojun.

176
00:10:32,360 --> 00:10:33,620
You've met her before.

177
00:10:36,000 --> 00:10:36,680
She

178
00:10:37,160 --> 00:10:37,880
is your

179
00:10:38,560 --> 00:10:39,440
girlfriend?

180
00:10:41,520 --> 00:10:42,650
She's just a friend.

181
00:10:44,800 --> 00:10:47,060
Isn't your sister at school in Shunyuan?

182
00:10:47,400 --> 00:10:48,530
Why didn't she come?

183
00:10:49,920 --> 00:10:50,600
She...

184
00:10:52,200 --> 00:10:53,440
She didn't know.

185
00:10:53,640 --> 00:10:54,640
I didn't tell her.

186
00:10:54,680 --> 00:10:55,610
She's too young.

187
00:11:16,520 --> 00:11:17,040
Fine.

188
00:11:17,280 --> 00:11:18,240
I'm going back.

189
00:11:18,800 --> 00:11:19,440
You should rest.

190
00:11:19,440 --> 00:11:20,200
OK.

191
00:11:23,360 --> 00:11:24,240
Thank you.

192
00:11:34,600 --> 00:11:35,400
Gu Yanzhen,

193
00:11:36,640 --> 00:11:37,720
Why you're back?

194
00:11:38,880 --> 00:11:40,410
Did I come at the wrong time?

195
00:11:44,360 --> 00:11:45,280
I'm leaving.

196
00:11:45,680 --> 00:11:46,560
Have some rest.

197
00:11:47,200 --> 00:11:47,760
OK.

198
00:11:51,240 --> 00:11:51,840
Hey,

199
00:11:52,480 --> 00:11:53,410
have some sleep.

200
00:11:54,000 --> 00:11:55,130
Don't talk too much.

201
00:12:05,000 --> 00:12:05,680
Step aside.

202
00:12:16,840 --> 00:12:19,120
Why are you two standing at the door?

203
00:12:26,400 --> 00:12:27,200
I'm going out.

204
00:12:27,640 --> 00:12:28,720
Where are you going?

205
00:12:28,720 --> 00:12:29,920
My stomach hurts.

206
00:12:29,920 --> 00:12:31,320
Need to use the bathroom.

207
00:12:53,440 --> 00:12:54,240
Come on in.

208
00:13:11,400 --> 00:13:12,520
You just came back?

209
00:13:15,440 --> 00:13:18,170
Shouldn't you be in Nanjing for your engagement?

210
00:13:18,760 --> 00:13:20,080
I managed to get out.

211
00:13:26,200 --> 00:13:27,840
Will you get into trouble?

212
00:13:28,400 --> 00:13:29,600
The news said

213
00:13:29,880 --> 00:13:32,040
your fiancee's family is powerful.

214
00:13:32,880 --> 00:13:34,280
Are you worried about me?

215
00:13:36,760 --> 00:13:38,160
You don't need to tell me.

216
00:13:41,200 --> 00:13:41,960
It's fine.

217
00:13:55,880 --> 00:13:56,880
How's your wound?

218
00:13:58,400 --> 00:13:59,400
Is it OK?

219
00:14:01,920 --> 00:14:02,680
I'm fine.

220
00:14:15,960 --> 00:14:17,080
I'm starving.

221
00:14:17,080 --> 00:14:18,610
Do you have anything to eat?

222
00:14:20,680 --> 00:14:22,160
You didn't bring me any gift

223
00:14:22,160 --> 00:14:23,320
but asked me for food?

224
00:14:23,320 --> 00:14:24,120
Seriously?

225
00:14:25,600 --> 00:14:27,130
I was on the train for hours.

226
00:14:27,480 --> 00:14:28,640
As soon as I heard you were in hospital,

227
00:14:28,640 --> 00:14:29,960
I came immediately.

228
00:14:29,960 --> 00:14:31,360
I didn't have time to eat.

229
00:14:53,720 --> 00:14:54,560
Stay here.

230
00:14:54,560 --> 00:14:55,560
Let me go check.

231
00:14:55,840 --> 00:14:56,500
Be careful.

232
00:14:56,760 --> 00:14:57,490
Don't worry.

233
00:14:59,000 --> 00:14:59,800
Liangchen,

234
00:15:01,240 --> 00:15:02,040
it's OK.

235
00:15:02,320 --> 00:15:03,780
They aren't coming for us.

236
00:15:06,520 --> 00:15:07,360
I'm here.

237
00:15:07,360 --> 00:15:08,290
No need to worry.

238
00:15:09,920 --> 00:15:10,680
Lie down.

239
00:15:31,440 --> 00:15:32,280
Mr. Gu,

240
00:15:32,520 --> 00:15:33,360
it's unsafe outside.

241
00:15:33,360 --> 00:15:34,490
Where are you going,

242
00:15:35,160 --> 00:15:36,040
Mr. Gu?

243
00:15:49,560 --> 00:15:51,160
What's happening out there?

244
00:15:51,240 --> 00:15:53,040
Workers of the Dadong Company are making a fuss.

245
00:15:53,040 --> 00:15:55,700
The Military Police have arrested many of them.

246
00:15:57,560 --> 00:15:59,360
It's OK. Nothing to worry about.

247
00:15:59,760 --> 00:16:01,760
Then I'll go back to my room.

248
00:16:11,560 --> 00:16:12,440
Do you have a knife in your bag?

249
00:16:12,440 --> 00:16:13,970
Let me peel an apple for you.

250
00:16:17,040 --> 00:16:18,840
Did you see Gu Yanzhen's face?

251
00:16:19,160 --> 00:16:20,560
I thought he was going to

252
00:16:20,560 --> 00:16:22,120
have steam coming out of his ears.

253
00:16:22,120 --> 00:16:23,680
I bet he's in love with you.

254
00:16:24,160 --> 00:16:25,160
What do you think?

255
00:16:27,440 --> 00:16:28,500
I'm talking to you.

256
00:16:30,160 --> 00:16:31,040
Is it lost?

257
00:16:31,400 --> 00:16:32,040
No.

258
00:16:32,040 --> 00:16:32,960
The yellow bag.

259
00:16:33,720 --> 00:16:34,580
The yellow bag?

260
00:16:34,680 --> 00:16:36,000
The one I told you.

261
00:16:36,200 --> 00:16:37,320
Those Japanese

262
00:16:37,320 --> 00:16:38,400
were after us for it.

263
00:16:38,400 --> 00:16:39,480
Isn't it inside?

264
00:16:43,960 --> 00:16:44,800
Where is it?

265
00:16:46,160 --> 00:16:47,160
Is it on the floor?

266
00:16:48,800 --> 00:16:49,560
No.

267
00:16:50,000 --> 00:16:51,130
Check under the bed.

268
00:16:53,880 --> 00:16:54,480
Nothing.

269
00:16:55,320 --> 00:16:56,200
Check again.

270
00:16:57,800 --> 00:16:58,880
It's not a big room.

271
00:16:58,880 --> 00:17:00,000
I don't see it here.

272
00:17:02,440 --> 00:17:04,310
Maybe you didn't put it in your bag.

273
00:17:04,310 --> 00:17:05,910
Perhaps Shen Junshan has it.

274
00:17:06,000 --> 00:17:06,520
Impossible.

275
00:17:06,520 --> 00:17:07,560
I saw it just now.

276
00:17:26,560 --> 00:17:27,280
Thanks.

277
00:17:28,520 --> 00:17:29,520
Go have some rest.

278
00:17:30,080 --> 00:17:31,880
You must be tired after the trip.

279
00:17:32,040 --> 00:17:32,800
I will.

280
00:17:35,520 --> 00:17:36,160
What's wrong with you?

281
00:17:36,160 --> 00:17:36,840
You want to die?

282
00:17:36,840 --> 00:17:37,840
Are you blind?

283
00:17:37,840 --> 00:17:38,240
What's your problem?

284
00:17:38,240 --> 00:17:39,200
-Are you looking for trouble? -You want to pick a fight?

285
00:17:39,200 --> 00:17:39,880
Can you afford it?

286
00:17:39,880 --> 00:17:40,840
You're dead!

287
00:17:41,560 --> 00:17:42,400
Speak!

288
00:17:42,560 --> 00:17:43,760
What's your problem!

289
00:18:21,280 --> 00:18:22,240
Crap!

290
00:18:22,960 --> 00:18:23,760
It's lost.

291
00:18:24,240 --> 00:18:24,920
How come?

292
00:18:25,320 --> 00:18:26,440
You said

293
00:18:26,680 --> 00:18:28,760
You've never left this room.

294
00:18:28,880 --> 00:18:30,940
That bag couldn't disappear itself.

295
00:18:31,360 --> 00:18:32,560
Think again.

296
00:18:32,760 --> 00:18:34,360
Who else has come besides me?

297
00:18:37,160 --> 00:18:37,880
Ms. Huo,

298
00:18:38,320 --> 00:18:39,000
Gu Yanzhen,

299
00:18:39,560 --> 00:18:40,440
Shen Junshan,

300
00:18:41,000 --> 00:18:42,040
and Jin Xianrong.

301
00:18:44,400 --> 00:18:45,040
Ms. Huo.

302
00:18:45,680 --> 00:18:46,740
Well, it's not her.

303
00:18:46,800 --> 00:18:49,280
Gu Yanzhen and Shen Junshan wouldn't take it.

304
00:18:49,280 --> 00:18:50,940
It could only be Jin Xianrong.

305
00:18:51,920 --> 00:18:53,800
What on earth is in that bag?

306
00:18:54,920 --> 00:18:56,040
It's important.

307
00:19:20,800 --> 00:19:21,760
Other things

308
00:19:22,040 --> 00:19:23,170
are in Warehouse 18.

309
00:19:24,040 --> 00:19:25,500
Have your men pick them up.

310
00:19:32,280 --> 00:19:34,880
It's always a pleasure to do business with you.

311
00:19:35,880 --> 00:19:37,240
Well, I'm thinking

312
00:19:38,680 --> 00:19:40,880
whether I should continue our cooperation or not.

313
00:19:40,880 --> 00:19:42,340
What makes you think that?

314
00:19:42,760 --> 00:19:44,440
Your ambition is big.

315
00:19:45,320 --> 00:19:46,720
I don't want to

316
00:19:47,840 --> 00:19:48,880
hold a candle for the devil.

317
00:19:48,880 --> 00:19:50,240
Devil is quite

318
00:19:50,880 --> 00:19:51,800
a strong word.

319
00:19:54,760 --> 00:19:57,040
Strong or not, I fear if it's true.

320
00:20:52,320 --> 00:20:53,040
If

321
00:20:53,320 --> 00:20:55,320
you have no intention to cooperate,

322
00:20:55,560 --> 00:20:56,440
then

323
00:20:56,840 --> 00:20:59,040
stop wasting my time.

324
00:21:00,760 --> 00:21:01,880
Mr. James,

325
00:21:02,560 --> 00:21:03,400
I'm confused.

326
00:21:03,560 --> 00:21:04,560
It's fake.

327
00:21:08,200 --> 00:21:09,840
Mr. James...

328
00:21:17,160 --> 00:21:17,800
Boss,

329
00:21:18,440 --> 00:21:19,880
were we set up?

330
00:21:25,280 --> 00:21:25,920
Did those

331
00:21:26,400 --> 00:21:28,260
Military Academy students do it?

332
00:21:31,000 --> 00:21:32,800
Those people on the train did it.

333
00:21:33,960 --> 00:21:35,160
What should we do now?

334
00:21:35,520 --> 00:21:36,400
Just let it go?

335
00:21:36,560 --> 00:21:37,480
Of course not.

336
00:21:41,360 --> 00:21:42,440
Whoever they are,

337
00:21:44,320 --> 00:21:45,780
they're simply handymen.

338
00:21:47,320 --> 00:21:48,580
That bag must have been

339
00:21:50,360 --> 00:21:52,560
in the Rong Mansion now.

340
00:21:54,240 --> 00:21:55,400
Are you saying...

341
00:22:00,560 --> 00:22:01,890
The third day next month

342
00:22:02,880 --> 00:22:04,680
